11 GENERAL SECTIONS
12 Sec. 201. In accordance with section 30 of article IX of the
13 state constitution of 1963, for the fiscal year ending September
14 30, 2026, total state spending from state sources under part 1 is
15 $152,000,000.00 and total state spending from state sources under
16 part 1 to be paid to local units of government is $0.00.
17 Sec. 202. The appropriations under this part and part 1 are
18 subject to the management and budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1101
19 to 18.1594.
20 Sec. 203. If the state administrative board, acting under
21 section 3 of 1921 PA 2, MCL 17.3, transfers funds from an amount
22 appropriated under this part or part 1, the legislature may, by a
23 concurrent resolution adopted by a majority of the members elected
24 to and serving in each house, inter-transfer funds for the
25 particular department, board, commission, officer, or institution.
26
27 DEPARTMENT OF MILITARY AND VETERANS AFFAIRS
28 Sec. 301. (1) Funds appropriated in part 1 for Selfridge Air
29 National Guard Base must be used to support costs of runway
ERE H01041'25 (H-2) e4ioyu

4
1 encroachment solutions while complying with air installation
2 compatible use zone program recommendations, including, but not
3 limited to, all of the following:
4 (a) Capital improvements necessary to shift the runway to the
5 north and repair the airfield and nonairfield features of the base
6 and surrounding community impacted by the shift.
7 (b) Infrastructure projects including, but not limited to,
8 roadways repairs, vehicle access to the base and to the museum,
9 stormwater drain and culvert repairs and modernization, force
10 protection features, airfield features, and taxiway extensions.
11 (2) Unexpended funds appropriated in part 1 for Selfridge Air
12 National Guard Base are designated as a work project appropriation.
13 Unencumbered or unallotted funds shall not lapse at the end of the
14 fiscal year and shall be available for expenditures under this
15 section until the project has been completed. The following is in
16 compliance with section 451a of the management and budget act, 1984
17 PA 431, MCL 18.1451a:
18 (a) The purpose of the project is to support costs of runway
19 encroachment solutions.
20 (b) The project will be accomplished by utilizing state
21 employees, contracts with service providers, or both.
22 (c) The total estimated cost of the project is
23 $152,000,000.00.
24 (d) The tentative completion date is September 30, 2027.
